                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/4437: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-06T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1923—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6—6:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>385. Following from commander of South China Patrol.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“December 5, 11 p.m. Local authorities today delivered to British consul
                        general reply to note from diplomatic corps. Reply states that [at] the
                        expiration of two weeks all payment of money collected by Maritime Customs
                        Canton to Peking Government must cease. Will transmit full text when
                        available. One Japanese destroyer arrived today and Italian gunboat expected
                        tomorrow from Peiho River. Leveson states he regrets I cannot join British
                        and French if action becomes advisable.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Admiral Leveson is commander in chief British China squadron.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
